>>> 07.01.2021
- Rewrote a number of monthly pulse and yearly pulse events to make them a bit more optimized by reducing the number of scopes they're run on.
- Updated ai_weight for a number of buildings to make them more compatible with Starnet AI.
- Added some support for non-default playable country types such as Real Space New Frontier's Ark origin.
- Removed old Automated Dreadnought combat computers. If you somehow were still using them... too bad.

>>> 09.01.2021
- Properly restricted flags for ESC dangerous tech research to playable empires.

>>> 10.01.2021
- Properly restricted flags for ESC dangerous tech research to playable empires for real this time (hopefully).
- Also added a global flag to prevent the crisis condition checker event from scheduling the crisis triggering event more than once per invasion cycle.

>>> 17.01.2021
- Fixed a bug where T-sized autocannons used MHD cannon's projectile.
- Improved and Perfected Dark Matter reactors should now reduce Juggernaut upkeep properly.
- Updated localizations for Juggernaut versions of T-slot weapons to hopefully make it clear that those X-slots are for Juggernaut only.

>>> 24.01.2021
- Normalize thruster speed bonuses across thruster tiers.
- Update on_tech_increased scripted effects for strikecrafts.
- Add support for planned standalone version of NSC Freebooters origin's flagship.
- Add components for ESC Overwrites Shroud Avatar designs.

>>> 07.02.2021
- Update reactors for the new version of NSC.
- Split battleship and titan reactors into NSC and non-NSC versions.
- NSC Exploration cruiser now uses NSC Battlecruiser reactors instead of NSC Carrier ones.

>>> 09.02.2021
- Fix NSC Battlecruiser reactors.

>>> 18.02.2021
- Further boost to NSC titan reactors.
- Upgrade fortress (tier 3 platform) reactors.
- Fix localizations issue with Juggernaut Matter Annihilator.
- Redo AI bonus customization:
    - Allow customization of AI special resources bonus:
        - Default is enabled.
    - Expand upon AI research speed bonuses. Following options are available:
        - Easy scaling (default)
        - Easy static
        - Moderate scaling
        - Moderate static
        - Challenging scaling
        - Challenging static
        - Disabled
    - NOTE: due to how the update was handled, in the on-going games AI will lose its research speed bonuses if those were enabled.

>>> 22.02.2021
- Updated Forgotten Queens Support

>>> 03.03.2021
- More Forgotten Queens Support
- Fixed a bug with repeated Unbidden invasions.

>>> 17.04.2021
- Updated the mod for Stellaris 3.0
- Add support for Nemesis DLC ship sizes.
- Use vanilla 'has resources to use component' triggers for component ai_weight.
- Fix descriptions for A.T. Field being not Evangelion-y enough.
- Fix missing ai_weight blocks for certain strikecrafts.
- Fix missing ai_weight modifiers for lack of resources on advanced jump drives.

>>> 23.04.2021
- Fix usage of global flags for crystalline entities that no longer exist in vanilla.

>>> 27.04.2021
- Fix one of dummy ship_sizes used to fix empty size_restriction bug not having designable = no.

>>> 16.05.2021
- Minor update to AI economic plans.
- Remove unnecessary string varibles for civics triggers.
- Expand the list of planet classes that allow construction of Mantle Mining Facility with more Planetary Diversity arcologies.
- Update hivemind pop requirements for Improved Mantle Mining Facility to match Stellaris 3.0.3 max tier capital pop requirements.
- Update icon for the Psionic Confinement building.
- Change tech weight modifiers for Time-Space Manipulation to make it a bit more accessible to console users.
- Add a few missing localization strings for modifiers.

>>> 19.05.2021
- Starnet AI compatibility update. For those without Starnet, this will make AI more eager to research ESC technologies.
- Export logic determining whether a country may research titanic/juggernaut X-slot weapons into a scripted trigger.
- Reduce number of jobs provided by Culture Nexus/Cerebral Node/Network Regulator a bit.
- Minor tweaks to repeated Unbidden invasions.

>>> 22.05.2021
- Empire that defeats the Ether Drake can now build a Dragon Hatchery building (empire-unique), which allows cloning of drake hatchlings.
    - Cloning a drake hatchling takes 360 days and will spawn it as a new fleet. These fleets can be merged and can have an admiral assigned to them.
    - Not available for Determined Exterminators.
    - Only Ether Drakes killed after this update will provide access to the technology needed for the Hatchery construction.

>>> 31.05.2021
- Buff health of X and T missiles.
- Normalize production and upkeep of ESC special resource jobs. Base production is now 2x higher to reduce the need for multiple buildings.
- Increase Zro and Dark Matter upkeeps of ESC buildings.
- Robotic pops without free will no longer can work Channeler jobs.
- Unemployed pops that worked ESC special resource jobs are now more likely to return to their former occupation if there is a new opening.
- Add starbase modules for ESC special resources, zro and dark matter.
    - Psionic Energy Collector can only be built in inhabited systems.
    - Some of these starbase modules have increased efficiency under certain conditions.
- Improved Crystal Farm now provides 4 jobs instead of 5.

>>> 31.05.2021
- Bug fix: new starbase modules are now properly available only when their respective technologies are researched.

>>> 04.06.2021
- Add "Psionically-Unified Society" technology that makes telepaths produce a small amount of Psionic Charges each month.
- Add "Psionic Overmind" technology that makes synapse drones produce a small amount of Psionic Charges each month.
- Add missing possible_pre_triggers to ESC jobs.

>>> 11.07.2021
- Mantle Mining Facility can now be built on New Frontier's Infernal Worlds.
- New icon for the Central Research Bureau building.

>>> 18.07.2021
- New titanic weapon added: Asteroid Thrower. Available immediately after researching titans, and acts as a kinetic counterpart to Perdition Beam.
- Fix overwritten Scourge strikecrafts not having armor penetration.
- Fix Ravaging Swarmers not having armor penetration.

>>> 06.08.2021
- Add support for Reastic Ships Necriod (which was missing for some reason) and Imperial shipsets.
- Integrate Chinese localization by Against War, Charles Chu and Zois Lee.

>>> 08.08.2021
